History.Return to Bregan D'aerthe:
{{Quote|There is little that escapes the notice of Valas Hune, my friend.|Jarlaxle Baenre.}}
Valas continued to work as a scout for Bregan D'aerthe over following decade. In the {{YearlinkName|1385}}, he accompanied [[Kimmuriel Oblodra]] on a mission to the small, ruined town of [[Carradoon]]. There they encountered a mysterious, interplanar rift. Unable to close the ''portal'', they merely retreated back to their headquarters.

He continued to serve as one of Kimmuriel's top lieutenants throughout the 15{{th}} century DR. Valas even reunited with [[Jarlaxle]] for a time, during his famed excursion into [[Gauntlgrym]]. The flamboyant drow vowed to take back the service of the "finest scout and thief" he had ever known.
